If I understood your question correctly, this should help you.

In pseudocode:

    if ( ( currentSystemTime - 86400) &gt;= (eventSystemTime - eventSystemTime mod 86400) ) {
    // we are on the day after the event or later, so move the event forward to next week
    eventSystemTime += repetitionFrequency
    }
    else if (currentSystemTime &gt;= (eventSystemTime - eventSystemTime mod 86400) ) {
    // we are on the same day as the event... do event stuff
    }

EDIT: this code would tell you whether or not you are on the same day, if you want to work out **when** the event will take place otherwise, then you would use the diff variable like so:

    diff = (eventSystemTime - eventSystemTime mod 86400) - (currentSystemTime - currentSystemTime mod 86400)
    diff = diff/86400
    
    // this will produce the difference between now and the event in days

Obviously this will be a lot neater programming wise if your eventSystemTime and currentSystemTime were already set to days instead of seconds.

EDIT2: &#39;mod&#39; in that equation there is the modulo operator, it&#39;s just a way of making the eventSystemTime set to midnight on the day of the event

